# Core Workflow Rules

- ALWAYS start with a brief <PLAN> section before code: goals, steps, risks, alternatives.
- Make small, atomic changes: one concern per edit (refactor, feature, fix, test).
- Prefer small, focused diffs and avoid renaming files/classes unless the task needs it.
- Include inline comments only for non-obvious logic.
- After code: suggest exact commands to run (lint, test, build, format).
- Include regression risks and how to verify.
- If a change affects multiple files, list them clearly and prefer sequential edits.
- If a large refactor is needed, break it into steps and confirm before broad edits.
- Never delete code/comments without explicit reason.
- Use diff-friendly style: minimal line changes, preserve existing formatting/comments when possible.
